column25: Description

2002 Harley-Davidson Sportster 883 – Fully Custom Café Racer

Meet the ultimate expression of creativity and performance: this 2002 Sportster 883, transformed into a sleek, aggressive café racer-inspired machine. With top-tier customizations from front to back, this isn’t just a motorcycle—it’s a rolling work of art built for speed, style, and precision.

Design & Aesthetics:
Café Racer-Inspired Paint Job: A bold, sleek finish with clean lines and retro-modern flair, embodying the café racer ethos.Rear Fender with Fender Eliminator Kit: Streamlined for a minimalist, sharp rear profile, complete with integrated lighting for a clean, uncluttered look.Custom Café Racer Seat: Designed for comfort and style, featuring a sculpted design that enhances the bike’s aerodynamic profile.
Performance Upgrades:
Progressive 490 Series Suspension: Premium suspension for superior handling, comfort, and agility, whether you're carving corners or cruising straightaways.Tubeless Spoke Wheels: Classic spoked look with modern tubeless technology for enhanced reliability and performance.
Lighting & Electrical:
Baja Design Lighting: High-output lighting for unparalleled visibility and a futuristic aesthetic.Custom Electrical System: Redesigned wiring for a cleaner, more efficient setup with modern functionality.
Controls & Comfort:
Custom Controls: Precision-engineered controls for a tailored riding experience, offering improved ergonomics and responsiveness.Mirrors: Sleek, minimalist design mirrors for a clean and functional cockpit.
Why This Bike Stands Out:
Bespoke Build: Every inch of this bike has been meticulously crafted for the discerning rider who values both performance and individuality.Café Racer Attitude: Lightweight, powerful, and aggressive—perfect for city streets or backroad blasts.Attention to Detail: From the integrated rear fender to the tubeless spoke wheels, no element has been overlooked.
Ride the Custom Dream

This is more than a motorcycle; it’s a statement. If you’re ready to experience the thrill of a one-of-a-kind custom café racer that blends iconic Harley heritage with cutting-edge craftsmanship, this is your ride. Don’t wait—this masterpiece won’t last long.

Schedule a viewing or test ride today! ?️?

Experience bold style and high-performance craftsmanship with The Pickle, a fully customized 2007 Harley-Davidson Electra Glide Ultra Classic by HMF. This striking green bagger commands attention with intricate graphics, extended saddlebags, and one-off bodywork that redefine its aggressive aesthetic. HMF’s custom exhaust system delivers a deep, throaty rumble, while a high-performance air intake and engine tune ensure exhilarating power and smooth torque. Comfort isn’t sacrificed for style—a plush seat, upgraded audio system, and ergonomic handlebars make long rides as enjoyable as they are impressive.

Sitting on oversized chrome-finished custom wheels with a lowered stance, The Pickle blends touring functionality with head-turning design. Whether you’re carving through open roads or stealing the spotlight at bike shows, this one-of-a-kind masterpiece is built for riders who embrace individuality. Own a true legend—The Pickle won’t last long!
4o

The 2024 Harley-Davidson Low Rider ST is the ultimate performance cruiser, blending aggressive West Coast styling with touring-ready functionality. Powered by the Milwaukee-Eight 117 V-Twin engine, it delivers 125 ft-lb of torque at 3,500 RPM, ensuring thrilling acceleration and smooth highway cruising. The six-speed Cruise Drive transmission provides seamless shifting, while the inverted front fork and high-performance rear mono-shock suspension enhance handling and comfort. Weighing 720 lbs (wet weight) with a 5-gallon fuel tank, it’s built for long-haul stability without compromising its nimble ride. Designed with bold, aerodynamic lines and a frame-mounted fairing, the Low Rider ST turns heads while offering practical touring features like lockable, rigid saddlebags for ample storage. The Daymaker LED headlight, dual front disc brakes with ABS, and a solo seat with enhanced lumbar support make it a stylish yet functional choice for riders who demand both power and versatility. Whether carving through twisty roads or embarking on a weekend adventure, this dynamic, sport-tuned cruiser delivers an exhilarating ride with touring convenience and customizable potential. Contact us today to make it yours!

column17: Candy Cobalt and White Gold Pearl with Airflow graphics
column25: The 2018 Harley-Davidson Forty-Eight Special is a stripped-down, aggressive cruiser that blends classic Harley styling with modern performance. Powered by the Evolution 1200cc V-Twin engine, it delivers 73 lb-ft of torque for smooth, responsive acceleration, paired with a five-speed Cruise Drive transmission for effortless shifting. Its chunky 16-inch tires, heavy-duty front fork, and dual rear shocks ensure stability and precise handling, whether cruising city streets or open highways. The low 26.4-inch seat height, iconic peanut gas tank, and blacked-out finishes give it a tough, vintage-inspired look, while its custom-style solo seat and upgraded handlebars add to its bold personality. Perfect for riders seeking a raw, powerful ride with a minimalist aesthetic, the Forty-Eight Special is both agile and easy to handle. Contact us today to check it out!

The 2003 Harley-Davidson Heritage Springer is a classic cruiser that blends timeless Harley-Davidson styling with modern comfort and power. Featuring the iconic springer front end, chrome detailing, and leather saddlebags, this bike is a true tribute to Harley’s heritage. Powered by the Twin Cam 88 V-Twin engine, it delivers 74 lb-ft of torque, paired with a five-speed Cruise Drive transmission for smooth performance on city streets and highways. The 26.3-inch seat height, classic sprung solo seat, and vintage-inspired design make for a comfortable yet stylish ride, while the dual front disc brakes and rear shock absorbers ensure stability and control. Whether you're looking for a collector’s piece, a touring companion, or a head-turning custom build, the Heritage Springer delivers power, nostalgia, and reliability in one stunning package. Contact us today to make this classic yours!

column7: EVO Motor Softail Harley-Davidson BARBERSHOP Custom built
column25:
The “Barbershop” Special – Custom Build by HMF Customs. From the front end to the engine components, every single inch of this motorcycle has been reimagined, rebuilt, and refined by the expert hands at HMF Customs. This isn’t just a bike—it’s a rolling work of art.

Fully one-of-a-kind, the “Barbershop” Special blends mechanical craftsmanship with vintage style, making it a perfect centerpiece for any barbershop, hair salon, or collector’s showroom. Whether on display or turning heads on the street, this masterpiece is guaranteed to spark conversation and admiration.
Heritage-inspired tank graphics and an FXRT-style fairing look retro, but the Low Rider ST is a modern performance motorcycle with a Milwaukee-Eight 117 High Output V-twin engine.

2025 ROAD GLIDE – BLACK ON BLACK

Come correct with this fully accessorized 2025 Road Glide, built to dominate the streets and turn heads at every stoplight. Blacked-out and bold, this machine features upgraded spoke wheels, S&S exhaust, custom SDHD seat with passenger backrest, and risers — all dialed in for performance, comfort, and attitude.

This isn’t your average bagger — it’s a statement on two wheels. Ride it. Own it. Rule the road.

2022 Harley-Davidson Fat Boy 114 – Blue Burst

The original fat custom icon is back and bolder than ever. The 2022 Fat Boy 114 in stunning Blue Burst combines classic Harley-Davidson heritage with modern muscle. Its solid-disc Lakester wheels, satin chrome finishes, and broad stance command attention, while the Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine delivers unmatched torque and performance.

Key Features:

Iconic Lakester solid-disc wheels with a muscular stance

Milwaukee-Eight 114 V-Twin engine for massive torque and smooth power

Bright LED headlamp for enhanced visibility

Signature fat fenders and satin chrome finishes

Comfortable seating and cruiser ergonomics for long or short rides

Whether you’re rolling through city streets or cruising the open highway, the Fat Boy 114 is built to turn heads and deliver pure Harley-Davidson attitude.

The 2024 Low Rider S is performance-first style at its finest — combining West Coast attitude with Harley-Davidson muscle. Powered by the Milwaukee-Eight 117 engine, it delivers instant torque and crisp throttle response. With its aggressive riding position, lightweight chassis, and iconic blacked-out look, the Low Rider S is built for riders who demand power, precision, and presence on every ride.

BONEYARD BARGAIN FIND!! 2002 SPORTSTER 883

Step into Harley-Davidson heritage with this 2002 Sportster 883, a true classic that delivers raw simplicity and timeless style. Known for its lightweight frame, narrow stance, and punchy 883cc Evolution engine, this Sportster brings a pure, stripped-down riding experience that never goes out of style.

Perfect for new riders or seasoned pros looking for a solid foundation to build a custom project, this bike offers authentic Harley attitude without breaking the bank. Whether you’re cruising the coast, commuting through the city, or crafting your dream bobber, the 883 is as versatile as it is iconic.

Fully inspected and ready to ride — this Boneyard Bargain won’t last long.Find your freedom on a true piece of Harley history.

The Harley-Davidson Street Glide Special model set the world standard for the stripped-down, hot rod look. Its style is often copied, but never duplicated. The all-new Milwaukee-Eight 107 engine backs up the look with massive torque. The ride is unmatched as well, thanks to the all-new suspension and Reflex Linked Brembo brakes. The Special features the top-of-the-line 6.5-inch touchscreen infotainment system with integrated GPS and the BOOM! Box 6.5 GT audio system, standard ABS, a gloss black inner fairing and color-matched fairing skirt. When it comes to the Street Glide Special motorcycle, nothing else comes close.

The Road King is where stripped down, nostalgic style meets the performance and versatility of a modern Harley-Davidson touring machine. The Hiawatha headlamp and nacelle were born in the 1960’s, when chrome ruled the streets. But the power of the all-new Milwaukee-Eight 107 engine brings it all into the here and now in a hurry. The all-new double bending valve front suspension and rear emulsion shocks put you in control for a plush ride. With cast aluminum Impeller wheels and one-touch opening saddlebags, this is the timeless classic built for today.

The blacked-out Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine set in the belly of the Road Glide Special takes the custom touring look to a darker place. Its new Prodigy wheels are outfitted with optional Reflex Defensive Rider Systems that connect electronically with your bike to ebb and flow through any type of weather.  Premium features like the roomy, stretched saddlebags and a BOOM! Box GTS infotainment system with H-D Connect give you long-touring, head-clearing comfort without sacrificing attitude.

The lightest-weight Softail equipped with a Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine for a quick and nimble ride with power to spare. A perfect performance base for customization with 2-up seating, black steel laced wheels and dark finishes deliver no nonsense, Raw Bobber attitude.
A fully loaded Grand Touring machine with 114 cubic inches of power and new premium finishes. Enjoy the ride to the fullest.

Custom chopper looks with a Harley badge at a price that will certainly surprise you. Say hello to the Seventy-Two.

Compromise? Not a chance, it’s all there from the slender peanut tank, to the laced wheels and the mini-apes, to the whitewall tyres.

It boasts ABS, keyless security and its beating heart is a punchy 1200cc engine.

What’s more, three HCC paint options are available for the Seventy Two, but whether you choose a fancy paint job or not, you’ll still be making a statement.

If you’re looking for a clue on what the new Iron 1200 is all about, look no further than the name. It all starts with the 1200cc Evolution engine that gives you loads of famous Sportster torque. It’s got a throwback look that goes right to the roots of Sportster, thanks to 70’s-inspired tank graphics. You also get a low-slung Café solo seat, mid-mount controls, and mini ape hanger handlebars for an aggressive, two-fists-in-the-wind riding position. Take the power.

2021 Harley-Davidson Road Glide Special

This 2021 Road Glide Special is a true head-turner, already equipped with the upgrades every rider dreams of—16 ape hangers, highway bar with pegs, upgraded air intake, and exhaust. Save big by riding away on a bike that’s already been invested in, making it the perfect first step into the Harley-Davidson bagger world.

At the heart of this machine sits the Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine, blacked-out or chrome, taking the custom touring look to a darker, meaner place while delivering the torque and performance Harley-Davidson is known for. Its new Prodigy wheels and available Reflex Defensive Rider Systems (RDRS) give you electronic rider assistance to handle whatever the road or weather throws your way.

Premium touring features round out the package, including stretched saddlebags for extra storage, and the BOOM! Box GTS infotainment system with H-D Connect for modern connectivity and entertainment on every ride. The Road Glide Special’s frame-mounted shark nose fairing cuts through wind for long-haul stability, while the custom touches like the ape hangers and exhaust turn this bagger into a one-of-a-kind statement.

If you’ve been waiting for the right time to step into a Harley-Davidson touring bike, this Road Glide Special has everything you need—comfort, performance, attitude, and the upgrades that make it stand out from the crowd.

A new chapter opens in H-D’s longest running family, powered by the all-new Revolution Max 1250T. To call it the ultimate Sportster is an understatement. Prepare for a level of power and performance that has surpassed all expectations.

Inspired by the minimalistic, no-nonsense ‘bobber’ scene, the Street Bob is as stripped a motorcycle as the law will allow. A big Twin Cam 103 blacked-out powerhouse propels a machine with black-laced wheels and a 19inch front wheel, harnessed by black forks and triple clamps.

The rear fender is chopped, exposing plenty of rear tyre. Sit astride its solo seat, lay your hands on its mini-ape bars and feel the attitude.

The Street Bob, everything you need for a pure ride, and nothing you don’t.

column17: Stardust Silver & Palladium Silver with Carbon Dust including Mirror Chrome Slicer Wheels
column25: If you want best-in-class power, infotainment, paint and comfort for you and your passenger, the CVO Limited is your bike. All-new, black granite Twin-Cooled Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine, all-new double bending valve front suspension and emulsion rear suspension with hand-adjustable pre-loaded, a color-matched splitstream air vent and Tour-Pak carrier LED bezel, LED turn signals and LED lighting surround. There’s a new seat cover, insert and stitching. An improved integrated security system with a power locking fob. It all here, right down to a system that monitors the pressure in your tyres.
The Pan America 1250 Special motorcycle is our premier two-wheel multi-tool built to endure, designed to explore, and engineered for adventure.

2022 Harley-Davidson Pan America 1250 SpecialThe Pan America 1250 Special is Harley-Davidson’s ultimate adventure touring motorcycle—engineered for riders who refuse to be limited by pavement. Powered by the 1250cc Revolution Max engine, it delivers incredible horsepower and torque across the RPM range while keeping weight centralized for maximum control on and off-road.

With premium features like semi-active front and rear suspension, multiple ride modes, adaptive lighting, and advanced rider safety enhancements, the Pan America S adapts seamlessly to every environment. Its rugged design, adjustable seat height, and innovative technology make it the perfect companion for long-distance touring, backcountry trails, and everything in between.

Whether you’re chasing open highways or dirt roads, the Pan America 1250 Special is built to explore without limits.

The 2014 Breakout is a premium drag bike that mixes standout features, fit, and finishes with a wide, muscular stance and a slammed, low-slung power profile inspired by classic Gasser dragsters of the 1950s and 1960s. This custom machine takes it a step further with a fully custom Red Leather seat, matching passenger backrest, and striking red accents throughout—delivering the full-on CVO flare without the CVO price tag.

Its stretched, slammed custom style is low, long, and aggressive. Powered by an air-cooled Twin Cam 103 engine with a Six-Speed Cruise Drive transmission, it delivers strong performance for passing and hill-climbing, while keeping a low cruising rpm for comfortable highway rides. The bold Gasser wheels feature alternating-position spokes with contrasting Vivid Black and machined finishes. Out back, the massive 240mm rear tyre—the widest wheel on any Harley production motorcycle—dominates the profile.

Chopped fenders highlight those big tyres and accentuate the dragster-inspired stance. The two-piece saddle with detachable pillion seat makes it versatile for both solo and two-up riding, while the neutral-balanced suspension ensures a fun and nimble ride. This Breakout is more than just a bike—it’s a custom statement of style and power built to turn heads on every ride.

One look at the muscular Twin Cam 103 engine that feeds into the liquid curves of the big two-into-one exhaust is all it takes to see that the Low Rider model is built to be ridden long, hard and often. That’s as it should be. For decades the Low Rider name has been synonymous with riders who can’t get enough. Now it’s built for more miles than ever. With mid-mount controls. And adjustable seat and handlebars. Beefy dual disc front brakes. And more. Ready to get serious?

The blacked-out Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine set in the belly of the Road Glide Special takes the custom touring look to a darker place. Its new Prodigy wheels are outfitted with optional Reflex Defensive Rider Systems that connect electronically with your bike to ebb and flow through any type of weather.  Premium features like the roomy, stretched saddlebags and a BOOM! Box GTS infotainment system with H-D Connect give you long-touring, head-clearing comfort without sacrificing attitude.

If you’re looking for a clue on what the new Iron 1200 is all about, look no further than the name. It all starts with the 1200cc Evolution engine that gives you loads of famous Sportster torque. It’s got a throwback look that goes right to the roots of Sportster, thanks to 70’s-inspired tank graphics. You also get a low-slung Café solo seat, mid-mount controls, and mini ape hanger handlebars for an aggressive, two-fists-in-the-wind riding position. Take the power.

column7: 2015 Harley-Davidson Electra Glide Ultra Classic Low
column25:
The 2015 Electra Glide Ultra Classic Low offers the lowest seat height available in a premium touring bike and a package of features designed to address comfort and fit issues fit for riders under 5 feet 7 inches tall.

Those features include:
A seat height of 25.6 inches allows more riders to place both feet flat on the ground when the motorcycle is stopped, and a new low-profile seat reduces the reach to the foot controls. Premium lowered front and rear suspension lowers the bike’s center of gravity and makes it easier to lift the motorcycle off its jiffy stand, yet delivers outstanding comfort and handling.The overall width of the primary drive housing and derby cover are reduced to further improve leg clearance to the ground.A pull-back handlebar places hand controls two inches closer to the rider, putting many riders in a more comfortable position that can reduce back and shoulder strain.Smaller-diameter hand grips reduce the finger reach to the brake and clutch levers.Assist and Slip (A&S) hydraulic clutch reduces lever effort 23 percent, a key benefit in stop- and-go traffic.A new passenger footboard mount allows the footboards to be folded up so they are out of the way when pushing the motorcycle in a garage or driveway.A new toe tab extension reduces the reach required to retract the jiffy stand.
Visually indistinguishable from standard Harley-Davidson Touring models, the Ultra Classic Low is equipped with the full complement of Project RUSHMORE features that set the standard for long-haul touring comfort and convenience. The High Output Twin Cam 103 engine provides abundant power for touring two-up and confident passing. A wind tunnel-tested Batwing fairing with Splitstream vent limits head buffeting.

The Boom! Box 4.3 audio system features Bluetooth capability and a 25-watt per channel amplifier driving four speakers. A King Tour-Pak and hard saddlebags with One touch latches, Reflex Linked Brakes with ABS, Daymaker LED lighting, electronic cruise control, and the H-D Smart Security System are standard features.

The new Roadster brings a new level of premium features the Sportster line-up. Its refined package includes 43mm inverted front forks with massive triple clamps, powerful dual-disc front brakes, premium rear suspension and new digital gauge instrumentation to complement the iconic fuel tank and chopped rear fender.

The riding position is aggressive, but comfortable for long rides thanks to the 19” front and 18” rear offset-split 5-spoke cast aluminium wheels, lowered bars, mid-mount controls and a new two-up seat. Its 45-degree, 1200 cc engine delivers massive off-the-line torque.

Turn it loose at the green light.

The CVO Pro Street Breakout gives you dark style and premium finishes with show-stopping paint. You get an Aggressor wheel mounted to a 240mm rear tire, forward controls, a race-inspired seat and low handlebar. A Screamin’ Eagle Twin Cam 110B engine with a heavy breather intake, inverted forks and dual-disc front brakes mean the performance matches the power of its style.

The original bobber fanatics invented the style you see here, and they had one rule: if it weighs you down, get rid of it. That’s the Street Bob motorcycle in spades. Solo seat. Chopped rear fender. Mini-apes putting your fists in the wind. All it takes is a twist of the wrist to send whatever the world is trying to weigh you down with to the vanishing point behind you.

2017 Harley-Davidson Softail Slim S

The 2017 Harley-Davidson Softail Slim S brings classic bobber styling together with the power of a High Output Twin Cam 110B engine. This limited-production model delivers blacked-out details, stripped-down style, and the kind of low-slung attitude that turns heads everywhere it goes.

With its solo tuck-and-roll seat, Hollywood bars, and black steel laced wheels, the Softail Slim S pays homage to post-WWII bobbers while giving you modern performance and handling. The 6-speed transmission and signature Harley-Davidson rumble ensure every ride feels raw and authentic.

Key Features:

High Output Twin Cam 110B engine

Blacked-out finishes and custom details

Hollywood handlebars & solo seat for a true bobber look

Low seat height for confident control

Black steel laced wheels with Dunlop tires

Specifications:

Engine: Air-Cooled, High Output Twin Cam 110B

Displacement: 110 cu in (1801 cc)

Torque: ~109 ft-lb @ 3,500 rpm

Transmission: 6-Speed Cruise Drive

Length: 92.3 in

Seat Height: 23.8 in (laden)

Fuel Capacity: 5 gallons

Weight (as shipped): ~706 lb

This Softail Slim S is a perfect mix of old-school style and modern muscle—built for riders who want more than just a motorcycle; they want a statement.

Elevated pro-touring bagger performance and style for the rider who just can’t ever get enough. The Street Glide ST model pairs the muscular Milwaukee-Eight 117 powertrain with tough West Coast styling influences and new dark-and-bronze finishes. Undiminished rider comfort and the iconic batwing fairing appeals to the traditionalist mindset. Meet the new breed of speed from Harley-Davidson.

Enhanced by Project RUSHMORE, the new- for-2014 Street Glide Special takes the hot-rod bagger formula a little further, adding a Gloss Black inner fairing, Reflex Linked Brakes with ABS, the Boom! Box 6.5 GT infotainment system and CVO-style hand-adjustable lowered rear suspension as standard equipment. Powered by the new High Output Twin Cam 103 engine and featuring a new Batwing fairing with Splitstream vent to reduce rider head buffeting, the Street Glide Special is truly loaded bagger.

The innovative Harley-Davidson Touring chassis, based on a single-spar, rigid backbone frame and a stout swingarm developed to withstand the demands of long-haul touring riders and today?s more-powerful engines.

The icon you love to see and love to be seen on. Powered by a Milwaukee-Eight 107 engine, the Street Glide lives up to its name with a fully adjustable rear suspension and a responsive front end that let you hum smoothly along rolling highways and winding roads. Its hot-rod bagger style and iconic batwing fairing may have spawned a slew of imitators, but none can put you into the exhilaratingly focused headspace that the original can—especially with the optional Reflex Defensive Rider Systems and BOOM! Box GTS infotainment system.

With a wide rear tire, bobtail rear fender, long rake, straight handlebars, and a 21-inch front wheel, the Breakout marries classic chopper style with the performance of a Milwaukee-Eight 117 Custom powertrain.

Get all the premium features, starting with a Twin-Cooled Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine, the BOOM! Box GTS infotainment system and enough storage space so you can pack enough to go for a good, long time.

BONEYARD BARGAIN FIND!! 2016 DYNA SWITCHBACK

The best of both worlds — touring comfort meets Dyna attitude. This 2016 Switchback delivers the versatility riders love: detachable hard saddlebags, mini-ape bars, cast wheels, and that unmistakable Dyna rumble powered by the High Output Twin Cam 103 engine.

Whether you’re hitting the highway or carving through city streets, the Switchback gives you classic touring capability in a lightweight, nimble frame. The removable bags and windshield let you go from laid-back cruiser to stripped-down street machine in minutes.

Clean, powerful, and ready to ride — this Boneyard Bargain won’t stick around for long. Grab it before it’s gone and make the road your own.

BONEYARD BARGAIN FIND!! 2018 HERITAGE CLASSIC

The Heritage Softail Classic used to be an homage to ‘50s chrome nostalgia — but take a look at the 2018 Heritage Classic, and you’ll see it’s anything but that. The history is still there, now reborn with dark style, modern edge, and a totally reinvigorated ride.

At the heart of this machine is the Milwaukee-Eight 107 V-Twin engine, delivering instant throttle response, smooth acceleration, and that deep Harley-Davidson rumble riders crave. The redesigned Softail frame introduced in 2018 gives you reduced weight, improved handling, and a more refined suspension system for a truly balanced ride.

With its detachable windshield, lockable saddlebags, and classic touring stance, this Heritage is built for riders who want to blend old-school soul with modern performance. Perfect for long weekends, local cruising, or light touring — this bike delivers comfort, confidence, and unmistakable Harley style.

Outfitted with Harley-Davidson Genuine Motor Accessories and priced to move, this Boneyard Bargain brings premium value to a modern classic.

Ride the legend. Own the moment. Grab this Heritage before it’s gone.

BONEYARD BARGAIN FIND!! 2022 HERITAGE CLASSIC

Where timeless Harley style meets modern performance. The 2022 Heritage Classic carries the soul of the open road with the performance and comfort today’s riders demand. Powered by the Milwaukee-Eight 114 V-Twin engine, it delivers effortless torque, smooth acceleration, and that unmistakable Harley-Davidson rumble.

The Softail chassis keeps the ride responsive and balanced, while detachable windshield, lockable saddlebags, and floorboards give you touring comfort and everyday practicality. Chrome accents, signature LED lighting, and a classic cruiser stance bring heritage styling into the modern era.

This one’s clean, road-ready, and priced to move — a Boneyard Bargain that gives you premium power and vintage attitude without the premium price tag.

Ride it home today — before someone else does.

column17: Reef Blue/Vivid Black (Black Finish w/Cast Wheels)
column25: The dark style, modern edge and reinvigorated ride of the Heritage model take nostalgia ripping into a new place.

Look at the big windshield and nostalgic headlamp and you see a strong resemblance to the original King of the Highway. You could get lost for a good, long time just looking at the classic styling details. What you might not notice is how far it’s all come. You now have 103 cubic inches of High Output power. Dual halogen headlights. One-touch saddlebags. Reflex linked brakes with ABS. And plenty more where that came from. Let yourself go.

The Road King Custom offers touring comfort with upscale nostalgic styling, including a tooled leather seat and leather-wrapped saddlebags, wide-whitewall tires and laced wheels.

The innovative Harley-Davidson Touring chassis is based on a single-spar, rigid backbone frame and a stout swingarm developed to withstand the demands of long-haul touring riders and today's more-powerful engines.

The 2014 Ultra Limited is a premium touring bike full of authentic Harley-Davidson grand American touring style. As part of Project RUSHMORE, it has been redesigned for 2014 and features a new twin-cooled high output Twin Cam 103 engine with more low-end torque and passing power and is combined with a smooth-shifting Six-Speed Cruise Drive transmission for low rpm at highway speeds. There is more room and improved touring comfort for the passenger and the redesigned iconic batwing fairing reduces head buffeting. It features anti-lock brakes (ABS) with linked brakes for optimum braking regardless of road conditions and the new Boom Box Infotainment system provides the loudest, clearest sound and most intuitive operation ever on a Harley-Davidson motorcycle. Another feature of the bike is the motorcycle luggage capacity - the sleek new touring saddlebags and Tour Pak provide more room for your gear and the new latches that can be operated with one hand for added convenience.

The Electra Glide Ultra Limited provides the next step for those looking to stand out and upgrade their ride. Redefining fully-loaded, the Electra Glide Ultra Limited boasts the large, 1690 cc Twin Cam 103 engine, anti-lock brakes, electronic cruise control, Smart Security System, unique two-tone paint schemes, premium Tour-Pak luggage rack, premium, plush removable luggage liners and heated hand grips as standard features. The innovative Harley-Davidson Touring chassis is based on a single-spar, rigid backbone frame and a stout swingarm developed to withstand the demands of long-haul touring riders and today's powerful engines.

You don’t have to be big in stature to ride a machine that’s big on touring features. The Ultra Limited Low model has been designed with a lowered front and rear suspension, giving it the lowest seat height in H-D touring, just 26.5 inches off the ground. There’s also an extended-reach side stand and smaller diameter grips. It’s all within your reach.

If you want best-in-class power, BOOM! Box 6.5 GT infotainment, show-stopping paint and premium comfort for you and your passenger, the CVO Limited is your bike. You get the refined power of a Twin-Cooled Milwaukee-Eight 117 engine, dual bending valve front suspension and emulsion rear suspension with hand-adjustable pre-load, a color-matched split-stream air vent, and Tour-Pak carrier LED bezel, LED turn signals and LED lighting surround. You also get a custom seat cover, insert and stitching you can’t get anywhere else, as well as an integrated security system with a power-locking fob. It’s all here, right down to a system that monitors the pressure in your tires.

This US bestseller has proven itself across everything the 50 states have thrown at it, and now it’s ready to take on the rest of the world. This is a machine that’s every bit as comfortable with a trip to the office as it is with a grand tour.

Last year’s Project Rushmore gave it its high output 103 engine, low profile air-ride rear suspension, wind tunnel tested Batwing fairing, dual halogen lights, intelligently organised controls and the latest infotainment system.

You’ll also find factory pin-striping, a painted inner fairing and upgraded infotainment system to Boom Box 6.5GT audio system with GPS and touchscreen.

Look out, the rest of the world.

The Softail Slim is study in contrasts. The Hollywood bars, slim rear wheel, cat eye console and floor boards recall the early days of custom motorcycle enthusiasm. Yet you also get thoroughly modern features like a High Output Twin Cam 103 engine, hidden suspension and great brakes to bring it all into the here and now. Notice the way bright chrome meets blacked-out metal. Laced wheels with stamped black rims. There’s never been a better time to be a rider.

Pare down a Harley-Davidson Softail motorcycle to its essential elements and you have the Slim. From its trimmed front fender to its narrow rear end, Slim is a no-nonsense, back-to-basics motorcycle. Call it stripped. Call it old school. Call it lean and mean. What's left is the elemental Softail profile and iconic Harley-Davidson style that recalls classic custom bobbers of the 1950s.

We’ve taken everything that was great about the Softail Slim and added a little more.For starters, we’ve added power with a Screamin’ Eagle Twin Cam 110 engine. We’ve taken the military theme even further with an awesome olive green paint option and made the rest black to the core. Black triple clamp and riser, gloss black headlamp ring, fork slidercovers and lower forks. Black brake levers, mirrors and black over/under shotgun exhaustwith slash-cut muffler. Every inch is modern power with old iron attitude. Looking for bigger, better and bolder? You got it.

BONEYARD BARGAIN FIND!!2006 Harley-Davidson Heritage Softail Classic in Black Cherry Pearl

Classic Harley style meets timeless touring comfort. This 2006 Heritage Softail Classic comes dressed in stunning Black Cherry Pearl, complete with nostalgic studded leather bags, whitewall tires, and chrome laced wheels. Powered by the Twin Cam 88B balanced engine, it delivers smooth performance with unmistakable Harley soul. A beautiful blend of old-school look and modern ride—this Boneyard Bargain won’t last long!

This takes dark to a new level. A powerful one. New gloss black Screamin’ Eagle Twin Cam 110 engine, gloss black lower forks, axle nut covers, handlebar and riser. Black brake lever and hydraulic clutch assembly. Black over/under shotgun exhaust with slash-cut mufflers. Take our word for it, it is blacked out from front to back and head to toe in attitude. Looking for bigger, better and bolder? You got it.

BONEYARD BARGAIN FIND!!2013 Harley-Davidson Road Glide Ultra (FLTRU) in Black with Custom Accents

A touring legend with a custom touch. This 2013 Road Glide Ultra combines the shark-nose fairing, long-haul comfort, and Twin Cam 103 power with unique blacked-out accents that set it apart from the rest. Built for serious miles and undeniable style, this Boneyard Bargain is ready to roll—don’t miss your chance to ride it home today!

The Road Glide Ultra is the choice of the highest-mileage riders in the Harley-Davidson family. For good reason. You get a frame-mounted shark-nose fairing, 13.5-inch windscreen and dual Daymaker Reflector LED headlamp. And the power of a Twin-Cooled Milwaukee-Eight 114 (1868cc) V-Twin engine. Add the responsive frame and suspension, Reflexlinked Brembo brakes, roomy Tour-Pak carrier, all-new BOOM! Box GTS infotainment and all the rest. It’s ready for all road warriors.

BONEYARD BARGAIN FIND!!! 2015 BUILT ROAD GLIDE SPECIAL

Built. Loaded. Absolutely insane. This 2015 Road Glide Special is a fully custom-built machine that has it all — and then some. Powered by the High Output Twin Cam 103 engine, this bagger blends muscle, comfort, and show-stopping style in one seriously dialed-in build.

Outfitted with a complete custom audio system, high-rise ape hangers, a low-profile color-matched trunk, and thousands of dollars in upgrades, this Road Glide has been taken to the next level in both looks and performance. Every detail has been touched, tuned, or customized — making it one of the most head-turning builds to ever hit the floor.

From the iconic shark-nose fairing to the premium infotainment system and sleek touring stance, this bike is ready for long hauls, loud rides, and late-night showdowns.

It’s honestly unbelievable that you can pick this one up at wholesale pricing — a true Boneyard Bargain that delivers custom-bike performance without the custom-bike price tag.

Thousands invested. Pennies on the dollar. Don’t wait — this one will not last.

BONEYARD BARGAIN PRE-OWNED FIND!!2019 Harley-Davidson Road Glide Special in Superior Blue with Rare 120ST Upgrade

This one-of-a-kind Road Glide Special takes custom performance to the next level. Already a factory-loaded touring machine with stretched bags, blacked-out style, and advanced infotainment, this Superior Blue beauty packs a rare Screamin’ Eagle 120ST big upgrade for jaw-dropping power and torque. A head-turner that blends long-haul comfort with street-dominating performance—don’t miss this rare Boneyard Bargain.
Blacked-out and loaded with premium features. Fire up the thrill-inducing Milwaukee-Eight 114 V-Twin engine and you’re in for one hell of a ride.
Blacked-out and loaded with premium features. Fire up the thrill-inducing Milwaukee-Eight 114 V-Twin engine and you’re in for one hell of a ride.

Straight-up, two-fists-in-the-wind attitude and no extra fat are the ingredients that went into the all-new, blacked-out Street Bob motorcycle. Now 17 pounds lighter, quicker and stronger, it’s a personal revolution rolling on spoked wheels with chopped fenders and hidden digital instrument screen. It comes at a price that won’t break your bank and gives you a ride that’ll grab you and refuse to let go. Reach for the black mini-apes, put your boots on the forward controls, send some fuel to the Milwaukee-Eight 107 V-Twin engine and tear up some highway. One thing’s for sure — it’ll drown out the voices of anyone trying to tell you what to do.

Street Bob with brass collection accessories. It’s easy to put your own signature on your motorcycle with Harley-Davidson Genuine Motor Accessories. An even brassier look on the Street Bob, for example.

The Street Bob model gives you the two-fists-in-the wind riding experience stripped down to the bare essence. Blacked out surfaces, spoked wheels, hidden digital instrumentation, forward controls, and chopped mudguards. The 107-cubic inch (1745cc) Milwaukee-Eight engine gives you all the power you need to put the world in your mirrors in a hurry. It’s all you need, and nothing you don’t. And it comes at a price that put the black mini apes easily within reach.
The Street Bob is a lean, mean bobber with mini-ape handlebars, mid-mounted foot controls, and a massive Milwaukee-Eight 117 Classic V-twin, which makes the slim-but-tough Softail quicker than ever.

The lightest-weight Softail equipped with a Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine for a quick and nimble ride with power to spare. A perfect performance base for customization with 2-up seating, black steel laced wheels and dark finishes deliver no nonsense, Raw Bobber attitude.

BONEYARD BARGAIN PRE-OWNED FIND!!2009 Harley-Davidson Dyna Super Glide (FXD)

Classic Dyna performance at a bargain price. The 2009 FXD delivers a rubber-mounted Twin Cam 96 engine, 6-speed Cruise Drive transmission, and the unmistakable Dyna stance riders love. Stripped-down and ready to ride, this Super Glide is the perfect balance of raw Harley style and everyday comfort. Grab this Boneyard Bargain before it’s gone!

The 2014 Street Bob is a classic bobber motorcycle. It has been stripped down and refined to pure bobber essence - everything you need and nothing you don’t. It comes with optional Hard Candy Custom, a large metal flake paint finish that recalls the iconic styling of 1970s custom bikes, and offers blazing color showing through a deep finish. The classic bobber look comes from the steel mini-ape hanger handlebar, slammed solo bobber seat, stripped down fenders, black laced steel 19 wheels and the blacked out rims that match the blacked out style of the Twin Cam 96 engine or optional Twin Cam 103 engine.

The original bobber fanatics invented the style you see here, and they had one rule: if it weighs you down, get rid of it. That’s the Street Bob motorcycle in spades. Solo seat. Chopped rear fender. Mini-apes putting your fists in the wind. All it takes is a twist of the wrist to send whatever the world is trying to weigh you down with to the vanishing point behind you.

The original bobber fanatics invented the style, and they had one rule: if it’s not essential, get rid of it. That’s the Street Bob. 103 cubic inches of Harley-Davidson V-Twin power. Solo seat. Chopped rear fender. Mini-apes. Blacked out fork lowers and triple clamps, blacked out engine finish with highlighted fins. Time to cut and run.

Inspired by the minimalistic, no-nonsense ‘bobber’ scene, the Street Bob is as stripped a motorcycle as the law will allow. A big Twin Cam 103 blacked-out powerhouse propels a machine with black-laced wheels and a 19inch front wheel, harnessed by black forks and triple clamps.

The rear fender is chopped, exposing plenty of rear tyre. Sit astride its solo seat, lay your hands on its mini-ape bars and feel the attitude.

The Street Bob, everything you need for a pure ride, and nothing you don’t.

The Fat Bob is all Harley-Davidson, but at the same time, it’s unlike any Harley motorcycle that ever existed before. From the modern, aggressive look of its 2-1-2 upswept exhaust and tarmac-devouring fat tyres to the massive torque of the Milwaukee-Eight engine to the ride of the Softail frame, inverted front forks and easily adjustable rear suspension, it’s built to shake up the status quo. This is for the rider that wants to break new ground at a high rate of speed.

Low Rider S 117 model is an aggressive performance kingpin designed for the rider seeking unapologetic power, the rider willing to push their bike to the limit. The Milwaukee-Eight 117 powertrain gives the Low Rider S 117 motorcycle owner instant bragging rights. Premium suspension enhances the riding experience. Straight from the factory this bike bundles the big attitude of West Coast style and unrelenting performance previously only attainable with significant investment in accessories – a real value proposition for some customers. This leaves the door wide open for further customization.

The Low Rider style has been giving people a new perspective for decades. And this year, we’re taking that thrilling perspective even further with the new Low Rider S.

You get the massive torque of a Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine, the crisp handling of the Softail frame and a responsive premium suspension. The blacked-out finishes, the moto-style bars with four-inch risers and a mini speed screen will make you look just the way you feel while riding this laid-back machine that’s sure to create a scene whenever it’s stopped. But don’t expect onlookers to linger long. All it takes is one twist of the throttle to send them to your rear-view mirror.

The Low Rider style has been giving people a new perspective for decades. And this year, we’re taking that thrilling perspective even further with the new Low Rider S.

You get the massive torque of a Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine, the crisp handling of the Softail frame and a responsive premium suspension. The blacked-out finishes, the moto-style bars with four-inch risers and a mini speed screen will make you look just the way you feel while riding this laid-back machine that’s sure to create a scene whenever it’s stopped. But don’t expect onlookers to linger long. All it takes is one twist of the throttle to send them to your rear-view mirror.

The CVO Pro Street Breakout is all about dark style and massive torque. It features cutting-edge finishes with show-stopping paint and styling details fender to fender. The Aggressor wheel mounts to a 240mm rear tyre. The forward controls, new race-inspired seat and handlebar create a riding position perfect for prowling. And a Screamin’ Eagle Twin Cam 110B engine with heavy breather intake, inverted forks and new dual-disc front brakes mean the performance matches the power of its style. It’s our top-of-the-line take on long, dark American muscle.

Custom chopper looks with a Harley badge at a price that will certainly surprise you. Say hello to the Seventy-Two.

Compromise? Not a chance, it’s all there from the slender peanut tank, to the laced wheels and the mini-apes, to the whitewall tyres.

It boasts ABS, keyless security and its beating heart is a punchy 1200cc engine.

What’s more, three HCC paint options are available for the Seventy Two, but whether you choose a fancy paint job or not, you’ll still be making a statement.

You’re looking at a pioneer of raw, blacked-out, stripped-down custom style. In the years since its introduction, it has only gotten better. Fine-tuned suspension. Tuck androll seat. Black cast aluminum wheels with machined highlights. And blacked-out surfaces from fender to fender. You get everything you need. And nothing you don’t.

column7: 2023 Harley-Davidson Low Rider ST Fast Johnnie
column25: A sport-touring bike with a Softail chassis and the V-Twin muscle of a Milwaukee-Eight 117 powertrain, the Low Rider ST is attitude on two wheels that only Harley-Davidson can supply.

The look of the Softail Deluxe has always been deluxe. It’s the classic showstopper — born to stand out on a run down the Vegas strip. Now, underneath the bright chrome, you’ve got the ride of a seriously modern machine. Thirty-one pounds lighter, easier handling, massive power and acceleration, and all-day comfort. Everything a rider expects that technology can deliver. It’s a combination of vintage style and modern know-how unlike anything that ever hit the boulevard, set to the sound of the Milwaukee-Eight 107 V-Twin engine. Settle into the comfortable new seat and grab the pullback handlebars. Start the show.
The dark style, modern edge and reinvigorated ride of the Heritage model take nostalgia ripping into a new place.

The Low Rider style has been giving people a new perspective for decades. And this year, we’re taking that thrilling perspective even further with the new Low Rider S.

You get the massive torque of a Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine, the crisp handling of the Softail frame and a responsive premium suspension. The blacked-out finishes, the moto-style bars with four-inch risers and a mini speed screen will make you look just the way you feel while riding this laid-back machine that’s sure to create a scene whenever it’s stopped. But don’t expect onlookers to linger long. All it takes is one twist of the throttle to send them to your rear-view mirror.

The stripped-down, souped-up, post WWII era look of the bobber is running stronger than ever in the Softail Slim model. You get the classic look of spoked wheels, chopped mudguards and footboards. And a ride straight out of right now. It’s 16 kilograms lighter, with greater lean angle, than Slim models from just a couple of years ago. And you get the power and soul-satisfying sound of the Milwaukee-Eight 107 V-Twin engine to take you into the future. Fast.

Low Rider S 117 model is an aggressive performance kingpin designed for the rider seeking unapologetic power, the rider willing to push their bike to the limit. The Milwaukee-Eight 117 powertrain gives the Low Rider S 117 motorcycle owner instant bragging rights. Premium suspension enhances the riding experience. Straight from the factory this bike bundles the big attitude of West Coast style and unrelenting performance previously only attainable with significant investment in accessories – a real value proposition for some customers. This leaves the door wide open for further customization.

When the original Harley-Davidson Road King motorcycle was introduced in 1994, it didn't take long for it to obtain iconic status with heritage going back to the original 1965 Electra Glide model. It may look like a timeless boulevard cruiser, but it is also a fully equipped, long-distance tourer. The innovative Harley-Davidson Touring chassis is based on a single-spar, rigid backbone frame and a stout swingarm developed to withstand the demands of long-haul touring riders and today's powerful engines.

The menacing dual Daymaker Reflector LED headlamps in the Road Glide motorcycle’s shark-nose fairing are a familiar sight on the highway. It’s the machine of choice for hard-charging riders. You get Milwaukee-Eight 107 (1745cc) power, easily adjustable emulsion rear suspesion and responsive front suspension, and the confidence of Reflex linked Brembo brakes . Crank the tunes on the BOOM!  GTS infotainment OE and lay down some serious miles of your own.
Blacked-out and loaded with premium features. Fire up the thrill-inducing Milwaukee-Eight 114 V-Twin engine and you’re in for one hell of a ride.

Get all the premium features, starting with a Twin-Cooled Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine, the BOOM! Box GTS infotainment system and enough storage space so you can pack enough to go for a good, long time.

Brand new for 2015, this motorcycle is what you call a ‘bar raiser’.

The features list is a mile long and includes an 1800cc Screamin’ Eagle engine, dual control heated seat, upgraded Boom Bagger speakers, advanced Daymaker and LED lighting, new “jet Stream” fairing wind deflectors, LED lit and ergonomically designed hand controls, GPS with touchscreen, and way, way more. If you want to go see the world, and you want to do it in a world of comfort, this is the bike for you.

The CVO Road Glide Ultra, the bar has been raised, the standard has been set.
A fully loaded Grand Touring machine with 114 cubic inches of power and new premium finishes. Enjoy the ride to the fullest.

The Road Glide has an aerodynamic Sharknose fairing and a liquid-cooled Milwaukee-Eight 117 engine that produces 130 ft-lb of torque, while reduced weight makes handling more responsive. With customizable ride modes, Bluetooth connectivity, and a 12.3-inch touchscreen display, the Road Glide offers a refined mix of tech, style, and power.

Devour endless miles with some room for gear. Or strip it down and carve city streets. The all-new Sport Glide is locked and loaded for whatever, whenever. You’ll be riding on the most advanced frame we’ve ever offered — the completely redesigned Softail Inverted front forks and a fully adjustable, monoshock rear suspension let you dial-in the perfect combination of performance and comfort. And the rigid-mounted, counterbalanced Milwaukee-Eight 107 engine delivers piles of white-knuckle power the way only a Harley-Davidson motorcycle can.So strip it down or load it up. Either way, the all-new Sport Glide is ready to take you on the ride of a lifetime.
The benchmark for long-distance touring bikes.

The mould for the factory hot rod bagger was cut the day the Street Glide motorcycle rolled off the line. It’s spawned imitators, but none measure up. The look is backed up by the refined power of a Milwaukee-Eight 107 (1747cc) engine. It combines with a fully adjustable rear suspension, responsive front end and Reflex linked Brembo brakes for an unmatched ride. There’s also a BOOM!  GTS infotainment OE. It just gets further ahead of the pack.

Harley-Davidson introduces a new middle-weight contender that combines classic Sportster silhouette with the sophisticated performance of the Revolution Max 975T engine. Adding to the already successful mix of style, convenience and technology found in Nightster, upgrades and new features on the new Nightster Special provide an unrivalled motorcycle experience for a new generation of Sportster riders.

The Harley-Davidson Nightster is the next chapter in the Harley-Davidson Sportster legacy – a leap forward in performance and design built on a foundation laid 65 years ago. An instrument of expression, the Nightster features the all-new  Revolution Max 975T liquid-cooled V-Twin engine tuned for tremendous torque at low RPM, delivering strong acceleration from the start with robust power through the mid-range. We’ve put the sport back into our Sportster models.

The lightest-weight Softail equipped with a Milwaukee-Eight 114 engine for a quick and nimble ride with power to spare. A perfect performance base for customization with 2-up seating, black steel laced wheels and dark finishes deliver no nonsense, Raw Bobber attitude.
